stateDiagram-v2
  [*] --> Absent
  Absent --> Live: put() (create, version 1 → StorageCreated)
  Live --> Live: put()/update() (version + 1 → StorageUpdated)
  Live --> Conflict: update()/delete() with stale expectedVersion
  Conflict --> Live: caller re-reads current version and retries
  Live --> Expired: TTL elapsed (expiresAt ≤ now)
  Expired --> Absent: lazily purged on next access
  Live --> Absent: delete() (→ StorageDeleted)

  note right of Live
    version is monotonic; optimistic
    concurrency compares expectedVersion.
    Writes serialize through the kernel
    mutex so read-modify-write is atomic.
  end note
